I"à9<h2 id="module-1-understanding-devops-culture"><strong>Module 1:</strong> Understanding DevOps culture</h2>
<h1 id="hands-on-activity-2-install-and-configure-your-repository-in-remote-git-in-github"><strong>Hands-on Activity 2: Install and configure your repository in remote Git in GitHub</strong></h1>

<h1 id="procedure"><strong>Procedure</strong></h1>

<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Create an account in Github</p>

    <p>Username should be your given initials and last name followed by -tip (e.g. ajcanlas-tip)</p>

    <p>Use your TIP email address for this (if you already linked your email with GitHub create a seperate one)</p>

    <p>Verify your account in your email in GitHub.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create a repository with your username (in my case it is ajcanlas-tip) without any files; and it should be public.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>In your Alpine VM clone the repository you just created in my case this is my url <a href="https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/ajcanlas-tip.git">https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/ajcanlas-tip.git</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create a profile with markdown this is a <a href="google.com">cheat sheat</a> in a ‚ÄúREADEME.md‚Äù file</p>

    <p>READEME.md should have the following:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>Your full name</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Year Level</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Interest</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Email Address</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>Computer Specs (CPU/Ram size/Disk type and size)</p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>To add it to your profile add the README.md file commit it then push it in the repository (to push a repository use git <em>push -u origin master</em>)</p>

    <p>Commands:</p>

    <p><strong>git add READEME.md</strong></p>

    <p><strong>git commit -m ‚ÄúFirst commit‚Äù</strong></p>

    <p><strong>git push -u origin master</strong></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Fork this repository <a href="https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git">https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git</a></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Clone your newly forked repository with <em>git clone</em> <em>https://github.com/&lt; your username &gt;/sysad2-12021.git</em> and go in the repository directory</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Make a new branch named ‚Äúactivity2‚Äù using <em>git branch activity 2 and git checkout activity2</em></p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Make a new new remote upstream with git</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Create a directory with your username, create a directory name ‚Äúactivity2‚Äù add the previous README.md file as HA2.md</p>

    <p>Command used:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>mkdir &lt; your username&gt;</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>mkdir activity2</p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>cp <path of="" your="" README.md="" file=""> HA2.md</path></p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>add, commit and push it to your activity2 branch</p>

    <p>Command used:</p>

    <ol>
      <li>
        <p><em>git add HA2.md</em></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><em>git commit -s n ‚Äúactivity2‚Äù</em></p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p><em>git push -u origin upstream</em></p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>Request a pull request for the master branch in <a href="https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git">https://github.com/ajcanlas-tip/sysad2-12021.git</a> and activity2 branch of your forked repository</p>
  </li>
</ol>

<h1 id="output"><strong>Output</strong></h1>

<p><a href="https://github.com/mlaabelong/sysad2-12021/tree/activity2">https://github.com/mlaabelong/sysad2-12021/tree/activity2</a></p>

